
# How to Build an MCP Client using LangGraph 🔌🤖

## Overview

An **MCP (Model Context Protocol) Client** allows a LangGraph agent to communicate with one or more **MCP Servers** and use the tools they expose. Instead of manually defining tools inside your application, the client dynamically discovers and loads tools from MCP servers.

This makes AI agents more modular, scalable, and easier to maintain. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

---

# What is MCP?

**Model Context Protocol (MCP)** is an open standard that enables AI models to securely connect with external tools, APIs, databases, and services through a standardized interface.

Think of MCP as:

> **USB-C for AI Applications**

Just as USB-C allows many devices to connect using one standard, MCP allows AI agents to connect to many different tools without custom integrations. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

